 hunger crisis inSyria, where people are dealing with shatteredinfrastructureand soaringinflation.\", \"from\": 3841, \"to\": 4030, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3882, \"end\": 3891, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm\", \"score\": 0.9999999905444383, \"rank\": 9.45034018499578e-09, \"text\": \"Stockholm\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stockholm\"}, {\"begin\": 3892, \"end\": 3899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling\", \"score\": 0.9999393759558964, \"rank\": 5.9777382756642496e-05, \"text\": \"Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cycling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A full6.7 million Syrians have been displaced, and 90% of the population lives in poverty, with64% relying on humanitarian assistance to survive.Here are some of the impressive Syrian refugee athletes we are cheering on during the Olympics:Alaa Massolived in Aleppo before he left the country in 2015.\", \"from\": 4031, \"to\": 4332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4049, \"end\": 4056, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugees_of_the_Syrian_civil_war\", \"score\": 0.9999999999904503, \"rank\": 9.315771067328648e-12, \"text\": \"Syrians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugees_of_the_Syrian_civil_war\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugees_of_the_Syrian_civil_war\"}, {\"begin\": 4208, \"end\": 4222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugees_of_the_Syrian_civil_war\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Syrian refugee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugees_of_the_Syrian_civil_war\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugees_of_the_Syrian_civil_war\"}, {\"begin\": 4290, \"end\": 4296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleppo\", \"score\": 0.999999999695774, \"rank\": 2.38807423792223e-10, \"text\": \"Aleppo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleppo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aleppo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He now resides in Germany where he continues his education and is a competitive swimmer.Muna Dahoukbegan practicing judo in Damascus at the age of six.\", \"from\": 4333, \"to\": 4484, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4351, \"end\": 4358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"score\": 0.9517469917731083, \"rank\": 0.05050947379776526, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 4457, \"end\": 4465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damascus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.664497489678494e-15, \"text\": \"Damascus\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damascus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Damascus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Forced to flee the country in 2019, she now lives in the Netherlands with her mother.Yahya Al Ghotany's sport is taekwondo.\", \"from\": 4485, \"to\": 4608, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4542, \"end\": 4553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999999959945853, \"rank\": 3.998762374357686e-09, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He now trains with the Taekwondo Humanitarian Foundation's Azraq Academy in Jordan.Both a long and triple jumper,Mohammad Amin Alsalamiwas born in Syria.\", \"from\": 4609, \"to\": 4762, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4632, \"end\": 4641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.824644051218822e-21, \"text\": \"Taekwondo\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\"}, {\"begin\": 4668, \"end\": 4673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azraq_refugee_camp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.976951826622313e-20, \"text\": \"Azraq\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azraq_refugee_camp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azraq_refugee_camp\"}, {\"begin\": 4756, \"end\": 4761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\", \"score\": 0.9999598292553479, \"rank\": 4.0172358014222605e-05, \"text\": \"Syria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Forced to leave his home country twice, he now lives in Berlin.SudanHunger has long been widespread inSudan, and when civil war broke out last year, things became even worse.Sudan's health system is under extreme stress andmillions of people face crisis levels of hunger, yetonly 30%of its hunger-related programs are funded.In this year's Paris games, two outstanding athletes originally from Sudan are competing on the Refugee Olympic Team:Musa Sulimancompetes in the 400 meter.\", \"from\": 4763, \"to\": 5243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5103, \"end\": 5108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999961942194, \"rank\": 3.805937410794418e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5157, \"end\": 5162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sudan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1970083501424121e-21, \"text\": \"Sudan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sudan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sudan\"}, {\"begin\": 5184, \"end\": 5204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999025354575, \"rank\": 9.746462616026844e-07, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team