hildren under five are stunted,meaning that chronic or recurring malnutrition is preventing them from reaching typical growth milestones.Here are two Ethiopian athletes participating in this year's Refugee Olympic Team:Eyeru Gebruis a cyclist from Ethiopia who moved toFrancein 2021 in order to escape conflict at home.Farida Abarogegrew up in Jimma and is passionate about running, football, and karate.\", \"from\": 5609, \"to\": 6091, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5837, \"end\": 5846, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999047672691, \"rank\": 9.390105865298241e-08, \"text\": \"Ethiopian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 5885, \"end\": 5905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999025354575, \"rank\": 9.746462616026844e-07, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 5935, \"end\": 5943, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999126885, \"rank\": 8.504367330866015e-11, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 6031, \"end\": 6036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimma\", \"score\": 0.9999961783396696, \"rank\": 3.8216748317055505e-06, \"text\": \"Jimma\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimma\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Forced to leave Ethiopia at a young age, Abaroge traveled through many countries before finally finding refuge in France.These athletes are a testament to what peop