tan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 20081, \"end\": 20089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peshawar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.332717512391302e-14, \"text\": \"Peshawar\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peshawar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peshawar\"}, {\"begin\": 20090, \"end\": 20098, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"score\": 0.9735640356032653, \"rank\": 0.027153801250856743, \"text\": \"Pakistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pakistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She is a judoka (someone who practices judo) and competes in the -70 kilogram category.Arab Sibghatullahalso practices judo, and his love for the sport began when he was eight years old.\", \"from\": 20100, \"to\": 20286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Originally from Kunduz province, he now lives in Germany.Amir Ansariis a cyclist.\", \"from\": 20287, \"to\": 20368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20303, \"end\": 20318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kunduz_Province\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kunduz province\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kunduz_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kunduz_Province\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Born in Iran, he grew up in Afghanistan before he was forced to flee in 2015.\", \"from\": 20369, \"to\": 20446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 20377, \"end\": 20381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"score\": 0.999999944264802, \"rank\": 3.9816039893050295e-08, \"text\": \"Iran\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iran\"}, {\"begin\": 20397, \"end\": 20408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanis