amiwas born in Syria.\", \"from\": 21215, \"to\": 21368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21238, \"end\": 21247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.824644051218822e-21, \"text\": \"Taekwondo\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taekwondo\"}, {\"begin\": 21274, \"end\": 21279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azraq_refugee_camp\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.976951826622313e-20, \"text\": \"Azraq\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azraq_refugee_camp\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Azraq_refugee_camp\"}, {\"begin\": 21362, \"end\": 21367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\", \"score\": 0.9999598292553479, \"rank\": 4.0172358014222605e-05, \"text\": \"Syria\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syrian_civil_war\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Forced to leave his home country twice, he now lives in Berlin.SudanHunger has long been widespread inSudan, and when civil war broke out last year, things became even worse.Sudan's health system is under extreme stress andmillions of people face crisis levels of hunger, yetonly 30%of its hunger-related programs are funded.In this year's Paris games, two outstanding athletes originally from Sudan are competing on the Refugee Olympic Team:Musa Sulimancompetes in the 400 meter.\", \"from\": 21369, \"to\": 21849, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21709, \"end\": 21714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999961942194, \"rank\": 3.805937410794418e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 21763, \"end\": 21768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sudan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1970083501424121e-21, \"text\": \"Sudan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sudan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sudan\"}, {\"begin\": 21790, \"end\": 21810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999025354575, \"rank\": 9.746462616026844e-07, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Born in Sudan, he moved to Cairo at the age of nine and toSwitzerlandin 2021.Jamal Abdelmajiis a track athlete who ran the 5,000m in the 2020 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 21850, \"to\": 22006, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 21858, \"end\": 21863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sudan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1970083501424121e-21, \"text\": \"Sudan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sudan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sudan\"}, {\"begin\": 21877, \"end\": 21882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.63019945702272e-15, \"text\": \"Cairo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cairo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He fled Darfur as a teenager and now lives with a host family in Tel Aviv, Israel.EthiopiaRecently one of the world'sfastest-growing economies,Ethiopianow faces one of the 10 worst food crises on the planet.\", \"from\": 22007, \"to\": 22214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22015, \"end\": 22021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Darfur\", \"score\": 0.6904552824847847, \"rank\": 0.4483197179713211, \"text\": \"Darfur\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Darfur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Darfur\"}, {\"begin\": 22072, \"end\": 22080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tel_Aviv\", \"score\": 0.9999999997148734, \"rank\": 2.8296429328695246e-10, \"text\": \"Tel Aviv\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tel_Aviv\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tel_Aviv\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Conflict and climate-relateddroughthave taken a toll.An estimated 40% of its children under five are stunted,meaning that chronic or recurring malnutrition is preventing them from reaching typical growth milestones.Here are two Ethiopian athletes participating in this year's Refugee Olympic Team:Eyeru Gebruis a cyclist from Ethiopia who moved toFrancein 2021 in order to escape conflict at home.Farida Abarogegrew up in Jimma and is passionate about running, football, and karate.\", \"from\": 22215, \"to\": 22697, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22443, \"end\": 22452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999047672691, \"rank\": 9.390105865298241e-08, \"text\": \"Ethiopian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 22491, \"end\": 22511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999025354575, \"rank\": 9.746462616026844e-07, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 22541, \"end\": 22549, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999126885, \"rank\": 8.504367330866015e-11, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 22637, \"end\": 22642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimma\", \"score\": 0.9999961783396696, \"rank\": 3.8216748317055505e-06, \"text\": \"Jimma\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimma\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Forced to leave Ethiopia at a young age, Abaroge traveled through many countries before finally finding refuge in France.These athletes are a testament to what people can overcome-but nobody should have to.\", \"from\": 22698, \"to\": 22904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 22714, \"end\": 22722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9999999999126885, \"rank\": 8.504367330866015e-11, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hunger is manmade, and the solutions can be, too.\", \"from\": 22905, \"to\": 22954, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Together, we can create a world where every life is well nourished.We hope you will join us in showing your support for athletes andrefugeesduring the 2024 Paris Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 22955, \"to\": 23131, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cheer them on, share their stories, and post about them on your socials.\", \"from\": 23132, \"to\": 23204, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Note the link between nutrition and performance in sports and in life, celebrate the talent that can emerge from hardship, and help bring attention to the tens of millions who still need support.\", \"from\": 23205, \"to\": 23400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After decades of conflict and growing climate stress,24 million Afghans, or nearly 60% of the population,need help to afford food and other basic necessities.\", \"from\": 23402, \"to\": 23560, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23466, \"end\": 23473, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9821422157706712, \"rank\": 0.015856275821494712, \"text\": \"Afghans\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Studies have shown that a majority of the population also is dealing with mental health challenges, which can be deeply linked to hunger.\", \"from\": 23561, \"to\": 23698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A number of athletes originally from Afghanistan are part of the Refugee Olympic Team.\", \"from\": 23700, \"to\": 23786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23737, \"end\": 23748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"score\": 0.9999997552909308, \"rank\": 2.447090337729667e-07, \"text\": \"Afghanistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Afghanistan\"}, {\"begin\": 23765, \"end\": 23785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999025354575, \"rank\": 9.746462616026844e-07, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We will be rooting for them:  Conflict has created a hunger crisis inSyria, where people are dealing with shatteredinfrastructureand soaringinflation.\", \"from\": 23787, \"to\": 23937, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A full6.7 million Syrians have been displaced, and 90% of the population lives in poverty, with64% relying on humanitarian assistance to survive.\", \"from\": 23938, \"to\": 24083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 23956, \"end\": 23963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugees_of_the_Syrian_civil_war\", \"score\": 0.9999999999904503, \"rank\": 9.315771067328648e-12, \"text\": \"Syrians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Refugees_of_the_Syrian_civil_war\", \"dbpedi